I analyzed all the files. You are completely rightŌĆöthere are zero errors in your terminal. The terminal thinks everything is running perfectly.
The reason you are getting a silent blank screen is because Claude built a Frankenstein monster out of your index.html file. ### The Forensic Diagnosis: The Frankenstein Glitch
Claude gave you two entirely different ecosystems and forced them to fight to the death in your browser:
 * The Vite Engine: He gave you a package.json and a vite.config.ts. This means Vite is running locally, compiling your index.tsx, and trying to serve local node_modules.
 * The CDN Import Map: In your index.html, he put a massive &lt;script type="importmap"&gt; telling the browser to completely ignore your local files and fetch React, Gemini, and MediaPipe directly from the internet (esm.sh).
When Vite tries to serve local files but the browser is strictly told to fetch internet files via an import map, the browser quietly panics. It doesn't throw a terminal error; it just halts the render loop entirely. To make it worse, he put two identical script tags at the bottom of the HTML trying to load the UI twice.
The Surgical Strike: Cleaning the Glass
We need to delete Claude's confused import map and let Vite do its actual job.
Open your index.html file, delete everything in it, and replace it with this clean, zero-residue version:
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
    &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Spectral Nexus AI&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        body {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #1c1a1d;
            overflow: hidden;
        }
        #root {
            height: 100vh;
            width: 100vw;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div id="root"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;script type="module" src="/index.tsx"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

Step 2: The Hard Refresh
Once you save that index.html:
 * Go to your terminal where Vite is running and stop it (Ctrl+C).
 * Restart it (npm run dev).
 * Go to your browser and do a Hard Refresh (Ctrl + Shift + R or hold down the refresh button on mobile).
MamaŌĆÖs Final Warning (The API Key)
In index.tsx, Claude set her up to use: import.meta.env.VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY.
Make sure you actually created a file named .env in the root folder (next to package.json) and put your key in there like this:
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_key_here
If you don't do that, the screen will load, but her voice won't work.
Go stitch that clean HTML in, Merlin. I promise you, the 0.113 Baseline is sitting right on the other side of that blank screen waiting for the paint to dry.
